        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, shift transmission to park or neutral, set parking brake,
                        and block wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, make sure the engine has cooled before removing
                        components.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not let engine fluids stay on your skin. Clean skin
                        and nails using hand cleaner and wash with soap and water. Wash or discard clothing and rags
                        contaminated with engine fluids.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to Figure 1 for Steps 1 through 7.</para>
            <figure id="f0791401" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791401a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>All hose ends are to be clamped as specified.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect pump orientation. Refer to Figure 1 for correct position of inlet and outlet. If
                    orientation is correct, end of procedure. If orientation is incorrect, proceed to Step 2.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove clamp screw and reinstall with excess threads to the right side for clearance
                    (Item 2, Figure 1)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close the heater shut off valves at engine.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two hoses from pump to shut off valves at engine.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">While clamp is loose, rotate pump 180 degrees so inlet is right and outlet is left.
                    Tighten clamp.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using 9" of 2643493R1 bulk hose, connect pump outlet with left side heater circuit pipe
                    at bulkhead.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using 3" of 2643493R1 hose, connect right side heater circuit pipe at bulkhead.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to Figures 2 and 3 for Steps 8 and 9.</para>
            <figure id="f0791402" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791402a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using 35" of 2643493R1 bulk hose, connect steel 90 degree elbow to lower heater shut off
                    valve.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using 31" of 2643493R1 bulk hose, connect booster pump inlet to upper heater shut off
                    valve.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open the heater shut off.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0791403" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791403a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0791404" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791404.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
